verses.text: Unto thee lift I up mine eyes, O thou that dwellest in the heavens.
Behold, as the eyes of servants lookunto the hand of their masters, Andas the eyes of a maiden unto the hand of her mistress; So our eyes waitupon the Lordour God, Until that he have mercy upon us.
Have mercy upon us, O Lord, have mercy upon us: For we are exceedingly filled withcontempt.
Our soul is exceedingly filled Withthe scorning of those that are at ease, And withthe contempt of the proud.
